}\section{\leftindent{
}\section{Creating a \typewriter{troff} inset}


}\leftindent{To insert a \typewriter{troff} inset into a working document, 
position the text caret where you want the \typewriter{troff} inset to appear, 
and select \bold{Insert Troff }from the }\italic{Special}\leftindent{ menu 
card or type:


<ESC><TAB> s\typewriter{troffet} <RETURN>


(the escape key followed by the tab key, then "s\typewriter{troffet}" when 
prompted for the name of the object, then the return or enter key.).  EZ will 
place a window at that point (See example above) to indicate the presence of 
the inset.  You may then all the usual EZ commands to put troff commands into 
this window.


}\section{Resizing a \typewriter{troff} inset}

\leftindent{
Position the cursor precisely over either the right or bottom border of the 
window, until the cursor changes to a set of arrows pointing in towards a 
line.  Click and hold the left or right mouse button, and drag the border out 
to its new position, then release the mouse button.


