\section{Printing and Previewing with \typewriter{troff} insets}\leftindent{

}
\leftindent{To see how the document will appear in the final printout, choose 
the \bold{Preview} option from the \italic{File} menu.  EZ opens a separate 
Preview window that displays a picture of the final document as it will appear 
 when printed.  For more information, see the \italic{preview }help document.


To print the document, simply select the \bold{Print} option from the 
\italic{File} menu, as you normally would.  For more information, refer to 
the\italic{ }help document on \italic{printing}.


}\section{Pop-up menu meanings

}
	\leftindent{When you're inside the Troff inset, you may notice that there's 
an extra menucard available, with the title 'stroffet'.  Here's a quick 
description of the commands available from this menucard:

}\leftindent{
\subsection{Close

}Close the currently selected inset.\subsection{


Open all}

Opens all insets in the current buffer.


\subsection{Close all}

Closes all open open insets in the current buffer.

